The Google Ads MCP server is an implementation of the Model Context Protocol that allows LLMs to interact with the Google Ads API [1][2]. The official repository [1] provides read-only tools for account discovery, GAQL-based searching, and retrieving metadata, metrics, and segments [2][3].

Several community-developed versions are available if you require write capabilities, such as creating campaigns, updating budgets, or managing keywords [4][5][6]. These often include safety features like approval workflows, dry runs, and budget guardrails [4][5].

To use the official server, add it to your MCP host configuration:

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "google-ads-mcp": {
      "command": "pipx",
      "args": [
        "run",
        "--spec",
        "git+https://github.com/googleads/google-ads-mcp.git",
        "google-ads-mcp"
      ],
      "env": {
        "GOOGLE_PROJECT_ID": "YOUR_PROJECT_ID",
        "GOOGLE_ADS_DEVELOPER_TOKEN": "YOUR_DEVELOPER_TOKEN"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

Consult your specific client's documentation for configuration file paths [2]. Ensure your environment variables, such as OAuth 2.0 credentials and developer tokens, are set according to your chosen implementation's requirements [1][4][5].
